G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1003.001,LSASS Memory,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) regularly deploys both publicly available (ex: [Mimikatz](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0002)) and custom password retrieval tools on victims.(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2)(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1074.001,Local Data Staging,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has stored captured credential information in a file named pi.log.(Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 19)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1037.001,Logon Script (Windows),technique,An [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) loader Trojan adds the Registry key HKCU\Environment\UserInitMprLogonScript to establish persistence.(Citation: Unit 42 Playbook Dec 2017)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1071.003,Mail Protocols,technique,"[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) used SMTP as a communication channel in various implants, initially using self-registered Google Mail accounts and later compromised email servers of its victims.(Citation: FireEye APT28)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1204.002,Malicious File,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) attempted to get users to click on Microsoft Office attachments containing malicious macro scripts.(Citation: Unit 42 Sofacy Feb 2018)(Citation: Accenture SNAKEMACKEREL Nov 2018)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1204.001,Malicious Link,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has tricked unwitting recipients into clicking on malicious hyperlinks within emails crafted to resemble trustworthy senders.(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1090.003,Multi-hop Proxy,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has routed traffic over [Tor](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0183) and VPN servers to obfuscate their activities.(Citation: TrendMicro Pawn Storm Dec 2020)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1498,Network Denial of Service,technique,"In 2016, [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) conducted a distributed denial of service (DDoS) attack against the World Anti-Doping Agency.(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1040,Network Sniffing,technique,"[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) deployed the open source tool Responder to conduct NetBIOS Name Service poisoning, which captured usernames and hashed passwords that allowed access to legitimate credentials.(Citation: FireEye APT28)(Citation: FireEye APT28 Hospitality Aug 2017) [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) close-access teams have used Wi-Fi pineapples to intercept Wi-Fi signals and user credentials.(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1003,OS Credential Dumping,technique,"[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) regularly deploys both publicly available (ex: [Mimikatz](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0002)) and custom password retrieval tools on victims.(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2)(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018)	"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1027,Obfuscated Files or Information,technique,"[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) encrypted a .dll payload using RTL and a custom encryption algorithm. [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has also obfuscated payloads with base64, XOR, and RC4.(Citation: Bitdefender APT28 Dec 2015)(Citation: Unit 42 Sofacy Feb 2018)(Citation: Palo Alto Sofacy 06-2018)(Citation: Talos Seduploader Oct 2017)(Citation: Accenture SNAKEMACKEREL Nov 2018)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1137.002,Office Test,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used the Office Test persistence mechanism within Microsoft Office by adding the Registry key HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Office test\Special\Perf to execute code.(Citation: Palo Alto Office Test Sofacy)
G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1550.002,Pass the Hash,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used pass the hash for lateral movement.(Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 19)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1110.001,Password Guessing,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used a brute-force/password-spray tooling that operated in two modes: in brute-force mode it typically sent over 300 authentication attempts per hour per targeted account over the course of several hours or days.(Citation: Microsoft STRONTIUM New Patterns Cred Harvesting Sept 2020)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1110.003,Password Spraying,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used a brute-force/password-spray tooling that operated in two modes: in password-spraying mode it conducted approximately four authentication attempts per hour per targeted account over the course of several days or weeks.(Citation: Microsoft STRONTIUM New Patterns Cred Harvesting Sept 2020)(Citation: Microsoft Targeting Elections September 2020)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1120,Peripheral Device Discovery,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) uses a module to receive a notification every time a USB mass storage device is inserted into a victim.(Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 19)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1598,Phishing for Information,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used spearphishing to compromise credentials.(Citation: Microsoft Targeting Elections September 2020)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1059.001,PowerShell,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) downloads and executes PowerShell scripts and performs PowerShell commands.(Citation: Palo Alto Sofacy 06-2018)(Citation: TrendMicro Pawn Storm Dec 2020)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1057,Process Discovery,technique,An [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) loader Trojan will enumerate the victim's processes searching for explorer.exe if its current process does not have necessary permissions.(Citation: Unit 42 Playbook Dec 2017)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1547.001,Registry Run Keys / Startup Folder,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has deployed malware that has copied itself to the startup directory for persistence.(Citation: TrendMicro Pawn Storm Dec 2020)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1114.002,Remote Email Collection,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has collected emails from victim Microsoft Exchange servers.(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1091,Replication Through Removable Media,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) uses a tool to infect connected USB devices and transmit itself to air-gapped computers when the infected USB device is inserted.(Citation: Microsoft SIR Vol 19)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1014,Rootkit,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used a UEFI (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface) rootkit known as [LoJax](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0397).(Citation: Symantec APT28 Oct 2018)(Citation: ESET LoJax Sept 2018)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1218.011,Rundll32,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) executed [CHOPSTICK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0023) by using rundll32 commands such as rundll32.exe “C:\Windows\twain_64.dll”. [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) also executed a .dll for a first stage dropper using rundll32.exe. An [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) loader Trojan saved a batch script that uses rundll32 to execute a DLL payload.(Citation: Crowdstrike DNC June 2016)(Citation: Bitdefender APT28 Dec 2015)(Citation: Palo Alto Sofacy 06-2018)(Citation: Unit 42 Playbook Dec 2017)(Citation: ESET Zebrocy May 2019)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1113,Screen Capture,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used tools to take screenshots from victims.(Citation: ESET Sednit Part 2)(Citation: XAgentOSX 2017)(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1213.002,Sharepoint,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has collected information from Microsoft SharePoint services within target networks.(Citation: RSAC 2015 Abu Dhabi Stefano Maccaglia)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1566.001,Spearphishing Attachment,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) sent spearphishing emails containing malicious Microsoft Office and RAR attachments.(Citation: Unit 42 Sofacy Feb 2018)(Citation: Sofacy DealersChoice)(Citation: Palo Alto Sofacy 06-2018)(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)(Citation: Securelist Sofacy Feb 2018)(Citation: Accenture SNAKEMACKEREL Nov 2018)(Citation: TrendMicro Pawn Storm Dec 2020)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1566.002,Spearphishing Link,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) sent spearphishing emails which used a URL-shortener service to masquerade as a legitimate service and to redirect targets to credential harvesting sites.(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)(Citation: ESET Zebrocy May 2019)(Citation: US District Court Indictment GRU Oct 2018)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1528,Steal Application Access Token,technique,"[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used several malicious applications to steal user OAuth access tokens including applications masquerading as ""Google Defender"" ""Google Email Protection,"" and ""Google Scanner"" for Gmail users. They also targeted Yahoo users with applications masquerading as ""Delivery Service"" and ""McAfee Email Protection"".(Citation: Trend Micro Pawn Storm OAuth 2017)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1573.001,Symmetric Cryptography,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) installed a Delphi backdoor that used a custom algorithm for C2 communications.(Citation: ESET Zebrocy May 2019)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1221,Template Injection,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) used weaponized Microsoft Word documents abusing the remote template function to retrieve a malicious macro. (Citation: Unit42 Sofacy Dec 2018)
G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1070.006,Timestomp,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has performed timestomping on victim files.(Citation: Crowdstrike DNC June 2016)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1134.001,Token Impersonation/Theft,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used CVE-2015-1701 to access the SYSTEM token and copy it into the current process as part of privilege escalation.(Citation: FireEye Op RussianDoll)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1199,Trusted Relationship,technique,"Once [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) gained access to the DCCC network, the group then proceeded to use that access to compromise the DNC network.(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1078,Valid Accounts,technique,"[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has used legitimate credentials to gain initial access, maintain access, and exfiltrate data from a victim network. The group has specifically used credentials stolen through a spearphishing email to login to the DCCC network. The group has also leveraged default manufacturer's passwords to gain initial access to corporate networks via IoT devices such as a VOIP phone, printer, and video decoder.(Citation: Trend Micro Pawn Storm April 2017)(Citation: DOJ GRU Indictment Jul 2018)(Citation: Microsoft STRONTIUM Aug 2019)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1595.002,Vulnerability Scanning,technique,[APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) has performed large-scale scans in an attempt to find vulnerable servers.(Citation: TrendMicro Pawn Storm 2019)

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1071.001,Web Protocols,technique,"Later implants used by [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007), such as [CHOPSTICK](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0023), use a blend of HTTP and other legitimate channels for C2, depending on module configuration.(Citation: FireEye APT28)"

G0007,APT28,group,uses,T1059.003,Windows Command Shell,technique,An [APT28](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0007) loader Trojan uses a cmd.exe and batch script to run its payload.(Citation: Unit 42 Playbook Dec 2017) The group has also used macros to execute payloads.(Citation: Talos Seduploader Oct 2017)(Citation: Unit42 Cannon Nov 2018)(Citation: Accenture SNAKEMACKEREL Nov 2018)(Citation: TrendMicro Pawn Storm Dec 2020)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1546.008,Accessibility Features,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used sticky-keys to obtain unauthenticated, privileged console access.(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach)(Citation: FireEye APT29 Domain Fronting)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1087,Account Discovery,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) obtained a list of users and their roles from an Exchange server using Get-ManagementRoleAssignment.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1098.001,Additional Cloud Credentials,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has added credentials to OAuth Applications and Service Principals.(Citation: Microsoft - Customer Guidance on Recent Nation-State Cyber Attacks)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1560.001,Archive via Utility,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used 7-Zip to compress stolen emails into password-protected archives prior to exfiltration.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1102.002,Bidirectional Communication,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used social media platforms to hide communications to C2 servers.(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)
G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1548.002,Bypass User Account Control,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has bypassed UAC.(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1553.002,Code Signing,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) was able to get [SUNBURST](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0559) signed by SolarWinds code signing certificates by injecting the malware into the SolarWinds Orion software lifecycle.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1195.002,Compromise Software Supply Chain,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) gained initial network access to some victims via a trojanized update of SolarWinds Orion software.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1555,Credentials from Password Stores,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used account credentials they obtained to attempt access to Group Managed Service Account (gMSA) passwords.(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1003.006,DCSync,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) leveraged privileged accounts to replicate directory service data with domain controllers.(Citation: Microsoft 365 Defender Solorigate)(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)
G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1005,Data from Local System,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has extracted files from compromised networks.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1140,Deobfuscate/Decode Files or Information,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used 7-Zip to decode its [Raindrop](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0565) malware.(Citation: Symantec RAINDROP January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1587.003,Digital Certificates,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has created self-signed digital certificates to enable mutual TLS authentication for malware.(Citation: PWC WellMess July 2020)(Citation: PWC WellMess C2 August 2020)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1562.002,Disable Windows Event Logging,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used AUDITPOL to prevent the collection of audit logs.(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1562.004,Disable or Modify System Firewall,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used netsh to configure firewall rules that limited certain UDP outbound packets.(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1562.001,Disable or Modify Tools,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used the service control manager on a remote system to disable services associated with security monitoring products.(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1078.002,Domain Accounts,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used valid accounts, including administrator accounts, to help facilitate lateral movement on compromised networks.(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1090.004,Domain Fronting,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used the meek domain fronting plugin for Tor to hide the destination of C2 traffic.(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1482,Domain Trust Discovery,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used the Get-AcceptedDomain PowerShell cmdlet to enumerate accepted domains through an Exchange Management Shell.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds) They also used [AdFind](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0552) to enumerate domains and to discover trust between federated domains.(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1484.002,Domain Trust Modification,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) changed domain federation trust settings using Azure AD administrative permissions to configure the domain to accept authorization tokens signed by their own SAML signing certificate.(Citation: Microsoft 365 Defender Solorigate)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1583.001,Domains,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has acquired C2 domains through resellers.(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)(Citation: FireEye SUNSHUTTLE Mar 2021)
G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1584.001,Domains,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has compromised domains to use for C2.(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1568,Dynamic Resolution,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used dynamic DNS resolution to construct and resolve to randomly-generated subdomains for C2.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1098.002,Exchange Email Delegate Permissions,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) added their own devices as allowed IDs for active sync using Set-CASMailbox, allowing it to obtain copies of victim mailboxes. It also added additional permissions (such as Mail.Read and Mail.ReadWrite) to compromised Application or Service Principals.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)(Citation: Microsoft - Customer Guidance on Recent Nation-State Cyber Attacks)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1048.002,Exfiltration Over Asymmetric Encrypted Non-C2 Protocol,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has exfiltrated collected data over a simple HTTPS request to a password-protected archive staged on a victim's OWA servers.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1190,Exploit Public-Facing Application,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has exploited CVE-2019-19781 for Citrix, CVE-2019-11510 for Pulse Secure VPNs, CVE-2018-13379 for FortiGate VPNs, and CVE-2019-9670 in Zimbra software to gain access. They have also exploited CVE-2020-0688 against the Microsoft Exchange Control Panel to regain access to a network.(Citation: NCSC APT29 July 2020)(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1203,Exploitation for Client Execution,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used multiple software exploits for common client software, like Microsoft Word and Adobe Reader, to gain code execution as part of.(Citation: F-Secure The Dukes)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1133,External Remote Services,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used compromised identities to access VPNs and remote access tools.(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1070.004,File Deletion,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) routinely removed their tools, including custom backdoors, once remote access was achieved. [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has also used [SDelete](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0195) to remove artifacts from victims.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1083,File and Directory Discovery,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) obtained information about the configured Exchange virtual directory using Get-WebServicesVirtualDirectory.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1070,Indicator Removal on Host,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) removed evidence of email export requests using Remove-MailboxExportRequest.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds) They temporarily replaced legitimate utilities with their own, executed their payload, and then restored the original file.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1105,Ingress Tool Transfer,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has downloaded additional tools, such as [TEARDROP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0560) malware and [Cobalt Strike](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0154), to a compromised host following initial access.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1090.001,Internal Proxy,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) configured at least one instance of [Cobalt Strike](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0154) to use a network pipe over SMB during the 2020 SolarWinds intrusion.(Citation: Symantec RAINDROP January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1016.001,Internet Connection Discovery,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used [GoldFinder](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0597) to perform HTTP GET requests to check internet connectivity and identify HTTP proxy servers and other redirectors that an HTTP request travels through.(Citation: MSTIC NOBELIUM Mar 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1558.003,Kerberoasting,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) obtained Ticket Granting Service (TGS) tickets for Active Directory Service Principle Names to crack offline.(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1204.002,Malicious File,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used various forms of spearphishing attempting to get a user to open attachments, including, but not limited to, malicious Microsoft Word documents, .pdf, and .lnk files. (Citation: F-Secure The Dukes) (Citation: FireEye APT29 Nov 2018)(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1204.001,Malicious Link,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used various forms of spearphishing attempting to get a user to click on a malicous link.(Citation: FireEye APT29 Nov 2018)(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1587.001,Malware,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) developed [SUNSPOT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0562), [SUNBURST](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0559), [TEARDROP](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0560), and [Raindrop](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0565)
column2: [SUNSPOT](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0562) and [SUNBURST](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0559) were tailored to be incorporated into SolarWind's Orion software library.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)(Citation: CrowdStrike SUNSPOT Implant January 2021)(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)"

column1: G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1036.004,Masquerade Task or Service,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) named tasks \Microsoft\Windows\SoftwareProtectionPlatform\EventCacheManager in order to appear legitimate.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1036,Masquerading,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has set the hostnames of its C2 infrastructure to match legitimate hostnames in the victim environment. They have also used IP addresses originating from the same country as the victim for their VPN infrastructure.(Citation: FireEye SUNBURST Backdoor December 2020)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1036.005,Match Legitimate Name or Location,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) renamed a version of [AdFind](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0552) to sqlceip.exe or csrss.exe in an attempt to appear as the SQL Server Telemetry Client or Client Service Runtime Process, respectively.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)(Citation: Microsoft Analyzing Solorigate Dec 2020)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1090.003,Multi-hop Proxy,technique,"A backdoor used by [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) created a Tor hidden service to forward traffic from the Tor client to local ports 3389 (RDP), 139 (Netbios), and 445 (SMB) enabling full remote access from outside the network.(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach)"
G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1095,Non-Application Layer Protocol,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used TCP for C2 communications.(Citation: FireEye APT29 Nov 2018)
G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1027,Obfuscated Files or Information,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used encoded PowerShell commands.(Citation: FireEye APT29 Nov 2018)
G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1550.003,Pass the Ticket,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used Kerberos ticket attacks for lateral movement.(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1069,Permission Groups Discovery,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) used the Get-ManagementRoleAssignment PowerShell cmdlet to enumerate Exchange management role assignments through an Exchange Management Shell.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1059.001,PowerShell,technique,"[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used encoded PowerShell scripts uploaded to [CozyCar](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0046) installations to download and install [SeaDuke](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0053). [APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) also used PowerShell to create new tasks on remote machines, identify configuration settings, evade defenses, exfiltrate data, and to execute other commands.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)(Citation: Microsoft Analyzing Solorigate Dec 2020).(Citation: Symantec Seaduke 2015)(Citation: Mandiant No Easy Breach)(Citation: FireEye APT29 Nov 2018)"

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1552.004,Private Keys,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) obtained the private encryption key from an Active Directory Federation Services (AD FS) container to decrypt corresponding SAML signing certificates.(Citation: Microsoft 365 Defender Solorigate)

G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1057,Process Discovery,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has used multiple command-line utilities to enumerate running processes.(Citation: Volexity SolarWinds)(Citation: Microsoft Deep Dive Solorigate January 2021)
G0016,APT29,group,uses,T1059.006,Python,technique,[APT29](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0016) has developed malware variants written in Python.(Citation: ESET Dukes October 2019)

G0080,Cobalt Group,group,uses,T1219,Remote Access Software,technique,"[Cobalt Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0080) used the Ammyy Admin tool as well as TeamViewer for remote access, including to preserve remote access if a Cobalt Strike module was lost.(Citation: PTSecurity Cobalt Group Aug 2017)(Citation: PTSecurity Cobalt Dec 2016)(Citation: Group IB Cobalt Aug 2017)"

G0080,Cobalt Group,group,uses,T1566.001,Spearphishing Attachment,technique,"[Cobalt Group](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0080) has sent spearphishing emails with various attachment types to corporate and personal email accounts of victim organizations. G0052,CopyKittens,group,uses,T1059.001,PowerShell,technique,[CopyKittens](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0052) has used PowerShell Empire.(Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017)

G0052,CopyKittens,group,uses,T1218.011,Rundll32,technique,"[CopyKittens](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0052) uses rundll32 to load various tools on victims, including a lateral movement tool named Vminst, Cobalt Strike, and shellcode.(Citation: ClearSky Wilted Tulip July 2017)"

G0070,Dark Caracal,group,uses,T1059.003,Windows Command Shell,technique,[Dark Caracal](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0070) has used macros in Word documents that would download a second stage if executed.(Citation: Lookout Dark Caracal Jan 2018)

G0012,Darkhotel,group,uses,T1553.002,Code Signing,technique,[Darkhotel](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0012) has used code-signing certificates on its malware that are either forged due to weak keys or stolen. column2: checks include the length of executable names, if a filename ends with .Md5.exe, and if the program is executed from the root of the C:\ drive, as well as checks for sandbox-related libraries.(Citation: Lastline DarkHotel Just In Time Decryption Nov 2015)(Citation: Microsoft DUBNIUM June 2016)"

column1: G0012,Darkhotel,group,uses,T1082,System Information Discovery,technique,"[Darkhotel](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0012) has collected the hostname, OS version, service pack version, and the processor architecture from the victim’s machine.(Citation: Securelist Darkhotel Aug 2015)(Citation: Microsoft DUBNIUM July 2016)"

G0009,Deep Panda,group,uses,T1047,Windows Management Instrumentation,technique,The [Deep Panda](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0009) group is known to utilize WMI for lateral movement.(Citation: Alperovitch 2014)

G0035,Dragonfly,group,uses,T1566,Phishing,technique,[Dragonfly](https://attack.mitre.org/groups/G0035) has used spearphising campaigns to gain access to victims.(Citation: Secureworks IRON LIBERTY July 2019)
